" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 472px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Uric acid reabsorption",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 452px; height: 318px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Model for urate (Ur-) reabsorption in the proximal tubule. This process begins with urate entry into the cell via a urate--OH- exchanger that is driven by the pH gradient created by the Na+-H+ antiporter. The reabsorbed urate then leaves the cell by carrier-mediated diffusion or possibly by anion exchange with an anion such as Cl-.",
